2
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:44,921
<i>In 1945, America's greatest generation
came back from war.</i>

3
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:49,646
<i>The flags of freedom fly over Europe.</i>

4
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:52,960
<i>Nazi Germany had been defeated...</i>

5
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:57,085
<i>...and 3 months later,
Imperial Japan surrendered as well.</i>

6
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,647
<i>And there's jubilation around this earth.</i>

7
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:04,169
<i>Men returned home. Among them,
some of baseball's most beloved names.</i>

8
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:07,449
<i>Musial. DiMaggio. Williams.</i>

9
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,251
<i>Life in the United States
could return to normal.</i>

10
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,289
<i>- What's the guy's name?
- What's on second?</i>

11
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:13,840
<i>- Who's on second?
- Who's on first?</i>

12
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:15,086
<i>- I don't know.
- Third base.</i>

13
00:01:16,440 --> 00:01:19,683
<i>And baseball was proof positive
that democracy was real.</i>

14
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,650
<i>A baseball box score, after all,
is a democratic thing.</i>

15
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:25,531
<i>It doesn't say how big you are
or what religion you follow.</i>

16
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,365
<i>It does not know how you voted
or the color of your skin.</i>

17
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:32,121
<i>It simply states what kind of ballplayer
you were on any particular day.</i>

18
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,924
<i>And he did it. It's a home run.</i>

19
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:35,923
<i>They knew he'd do it.</i>

20
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:39,323
<i>African Americans
had served their country gallantly.</i>

21
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:42,529
<i>They returned home from fighting
to free the world from tyranny...</i>

22
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:46,526
<i>...only to find racism, segregation
and Jim Crow law still waiting at home.</i>

23
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:49,047
<i>Segregation was the law...</i>

24
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,443
<i>...and no group was more scrupulous
in its observance of custom...</i>

25
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,170
<i>...than organized baseball.</i>

26
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:55,760
<i>There was a long road ahead.</i>

27
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,887
<i>If African Americans dreamed
of playing baseball...</i>

28
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,690
<i>...it was not for the Yankees...</i>

29
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:07,208
<i>...but for teams like the Kansas City
Monarchs of the Negro Leagues...</i>

30
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:11,001
<i>...where the barnstorming style of play
stood in contrast to the Majors.</i>

31
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:14,330
<i>In 1946, there were
16 Major League baseball teams...</i>

32
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:17,882
<i>...with a total of 400 players
on their rosters.</i>

33
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:20,691
<i>Every one of the 400 players
were white.</i>

34
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:26,529
<i>But when opening day came in 1947,
that number dropped to 399...</i>

35
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,603
<i>...and one man stood apart.</i>

36
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:52,529
Gentlemen, I have a plan.

37
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:56,611
Plan's good, Mr. Rickey.
You always have one.

38
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,445
My wife says I'm too old. Heh, heh.

39
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:04,045
That my health's not up to it.

40
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:09,121
My son says, uh, everybody in...

41
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:14,290
Everybody in baseball
is gonna be against me. Heh.

42
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,522
But I'm gonna do it.

43
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,602
Do what, Mr. Rickey?

44
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:25,808
I'm gonna bring a Negro ballplayer...

45
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,451
...to the Brooklyn Dodgers.

46
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:40,125
With all due respect, sir,
have you lost your mind?

47
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:44,406
Think... Think about...

48
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,086
Think about the abuse...

49
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,527
...that you are gonna take
from the newspapers...

50
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:52,524
...let alone how this is gonna play out
in Flatbush!

51
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,809
Please, Mr. Rickey.

52
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,963
Sit down, Harold.

53
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:07,491
No law against it, Clyde.

54
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,965
No.

55
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,801
No, but there's a code.

56
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:17,527
You break a law and get away with it,
some people think you're smart.

57
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,401
You break an unwritten law...

58
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,001
...you'll be an outcast.

59
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,201
Mm-hm.

60
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,364
So be it.

61
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:34,446
New York's full of Negro baseball fans.

62
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:41,121
Dollars aren't black and white,
they're green.

63
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:43,726
Every dollar's green.

64
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,248
I don't know who he is...

65
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,883
...or where he is...

66
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,643
...but he's coming.

67
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,811
Hey, runner!

68
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:02,169
Where'd you learn to move like that,
at a dime-a-dance night?

69
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,850
Stand still!

70
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,411
There you are!

71
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:07,881
Ball!

72
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,484
Safe!

73
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,526
Catcher!

74
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,569
When you gonna start throwing for real?

75
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,006
You talking to me?

76
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,162
You got a rag arm, catcher.

77
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:22,530
Steal home.
You'll find out what kind of arm I got.

78
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,444
Okay.

79
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,766
I'm coming.

80
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,764
Where's your shortstop from?

81
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,081
California.

82
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:32,402
Sure got a mouth on him.

83
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,407
<i>Safe!</i>

84
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:59,769
<i>Discussions
concerning Japan's offer of surrender.</i>

85
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,406
<i>Washington, London, Moscow,
and Chungking...</i>

86
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,608
<i>...now framing their decision.</i>

87
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:08,122
<i>When this decision will be communicated
to Tokyo via the government's...</i>

88
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:10,647
- Fill her up?
- Yes, sir.

89
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:16,451
You boys heading out?
Uh, Chicago.

90
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,409
Chicago, huh? Heh.

91
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:22,283
- You boys get around.
- Yeah, we sure do.

92
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:27,563
- Hey. Hey, you, where you going?
- To the toilet.

93
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:31,410
Hell, come on, boy.
You know you can't go in there.

94
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:42,123
Them Cokes are a nickel.

95
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,645
Take that hose out of the tank.

96
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,484
- Robinson.
- What?

97
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,969
I said take it out.

98
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,685
We'll get our 99 gallons of gas
someplace else.

99
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:18,525
All right, then. Go on.

100
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,450
Go on! Use it.

101
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,484
Roy Campanella.

102
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:31,168
Hell of a player. He's too sweet.
They'd eat him alive.

103
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,810
All right.

104
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:36,282
Oh, sorry. Oh, wait. Sorry.

105
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,723
- Satchel Paige, then.
- He's too old.

106
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,362
We need a player with a future,
not a past.

107
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,925
Here.

108
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,809
Jack Roosevelt Robinson.

109
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:53,407
4-sport college man, out of UCLA.
That means he's played with white boys.

110
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,724
Playing for the Kansas City Monarchs.

111
00:07:56,880 --> 00:08:00,407
26 years old.
He's batting .350. 3-50.

112
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,363
Methodist.

113
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,851
Commissioned Army officer.

114
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,371
He was court-martialed.

115
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,090
<i>He's a troublemaker.</i>

116
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,567
<i>Well, he argues with umpires.</i>

117
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,524
<i>A quick temper is his reputation.</i>

118
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,600
<i>Well, what was he court-martialed for?</i>

119
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:20,009
<i>Wouldn't sit in the back
of a military bus. Fort Hood, Texas.</i>

120
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:23,084
Driver asked him to, uh, move back.

121
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,768
MPs had to take him off.

122
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,846
There, you see?

123
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,163
I see he resents segregation.

124
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:37,688
If he were white, we'd call that spirit.

125
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,691
Robinson's a Methodist.

126
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,763
I'm a Methodist. God's a Methodist.

127
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:47,089
We can't go wrong. Find him.

128
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,404
Bring him here.

129
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:54,600
How are you, fellas?
I'm looking for your, uh, shortstop.

130
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,121
You Jackie Robinson?

131
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,484
Who are you?

132
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:11,926
<i>Mr. Rickey.</i>

133
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,250
What's this about?

134
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,606
This is about baseball, Jackie.

135
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:38,684
I see you starting in spring
with our affiliate in Montreal.

136
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,968
If you make it there...

137
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,688
...we'll try you down here...

138
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,241
...with the Dodgers.

139
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,966
With the white Brooklyn Dodgers.

140
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,523
Hmm.

141
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:58,490
I'll pay you $600 a month.

142
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:03,762
And a $3500 bonus
when you sign the contract.

143
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:04,967
That agreeable?

144
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:09,444
- Yes, that's fine but...
- There's one condition.

145
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:13,770
I know you can hit behind the runner.
That you can read a pitch.

146
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,327
One question is...

147
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:18,528
...can you control your temper?

148
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,487
My temper?

149
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,967
Yes, your temper! What are you, deaf?

150
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:28,726
A black man in white baseball, heh,
can you imagine the reaction?

151
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:31,008
The vitriol?

152
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:38,567
Dodgers check into a hotel,
a, uh, a decent, good hotel.

153
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:41,041
You're worn out from the road.

154
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,926
Some clerk won't give you the pen
to sign in with.

155
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:49,682
"We got no room for you, boy. Not even
down in the coal bin where you belong."

156
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:53,811
Team stops at a restaurant.
Waiter won't take your order.

157
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,891
"Didn't you see the sign on the door?
No niggers allowed."

158
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:01,840
What are you gonna do then?
Fight him? Ruin all my plans?

159
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:06,040
Answer me, you black son of a bitch!

160
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:14,605
You want a player who doesn't
have the guts to fight back?

161
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,725
No.

162
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,605
No.

163
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:26,088
I want a player who's got the guts
not to fight back.

164
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,767
People aren't gonna like this.

165
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:34,040
They're gonna do anything
to get you to react.

166
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:38,125
Echo a curse with a curse
and, uh, they'll hear only yours.

167
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:42,968
Follow a blow with a blow and they'll say,
"The Negro lost his temper."

168
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:46,169
That "The Negro does not belong."

169
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,641
Your enemy will be out in force...

170
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:52,247
...and you cannot meet him
on his own low ground.

171
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:56,964
We win with hitting, running, fielding.
Only that.

172
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:01,330
We win if the world is convinced
of two things:

173
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:05,804
That you are a fine gentleman
and a great baseball player.

174
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,527
Like our Savior...

175
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:15,162
...you gotta have the guts...

176
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,649
...to turn the other cheek.

177
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,409
Can you do it?

178
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:40,561
You give me a uniform...

179
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:47,208
...you give me a, heh,
number on my back...

180
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,362
...and I'll give you the guts.

181
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,446
Hello?

182
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,011
<i>Rae...</i>

183
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,005
Jack.

184
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,050
I'm in Brooklyn.

185
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,841
Brooklyn? For what?

186
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,729
Uh...

187
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:16,804
I don't want to say on the phone.

188
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:20,682
In fact, I'm not supposed to tell anyone.

189
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:25,565
What's going on? Aren't you supposed
to be playing in Chicago?

190
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,683
We've been tested, you and me.

191
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:35,687
<i>We've done everything
the right way. We have.</i>

192
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:41,121
Me trying to make money,
you finishing school.

193
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,724
We don't owe the world a thing.

194
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,611
<i>Only each other.</i>

195
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:49,566
Jack, what are you talking about?
What is going on? What happened?

196
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,410
Will you marry me, Rae?

197
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,925
Absolutely.

198
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:01,931
Yes. Yes.

199
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:05,607
When?

200
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,524
Um...

201
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,762
How about right now?

202
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,048
Did my mom look happy?

203
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:21,407
Yes. You know your mother loves me.

204
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,282
Did my gram look happy?

205
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,210
Yes.

206
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,211
My brother look happy?

207
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:36,328
- Heh, your brother?
- Ha, ha.

208
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:41,968
Everyone looked happy. I've never seen
so many happy-looking people.

209
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,688
Did Jack Robinson look happy?

210
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,689
What if I can't make you happy?

211
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,650
Too late.

212
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,809
You already do.

213
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,488
It's you and me, Rae.

214
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,889
Ooh, ha, ha.

215
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,042
Um...

216
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:14,767
- Till the wheels fall off.
- Hmm.

217
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:19,164
Oh, Jack, the world is waiting for us.

218
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:22,767
The world can wait one more night.

219
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,840
Are you coming, Mrs. Robinson?

220
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,691
I'd follow you anywhere, Mr. Robinson.

221
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,805
Okay.

222
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,124
Okay.

223
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:48,041
<i>Flight to Pensacola leaves in an hour.</i>

224
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,521
<i>Flight to Pensacola leaves in an hour.</i>

225
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:55,761
"Flight to Pensacola leaves in an hour.
Flight to Pensacola leaves in an hour."

226
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,045
Are you okay?

227
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:02,682
I've just never seen one before.

228
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:06,405
Oh.

229
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:10,690
Yeah, we're not in Pasadena anymore.

230
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,885
Rae?

231
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:19,407
Rae?

232
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,730
Rae!

233
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,642
Oh, boy.

234
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,761
We have to lighten the plane.

235
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:41,046
There's some bad weather east of here.

236
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,931
A heavy plane is dangerous.

237
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:47,568
So someone'll have to cancel.

238
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:51,770
Look, I'm with the Brooklyn Dodger
organization.

239
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,331
I have to get down to Daytona.

240
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:56,086
I'm supposed to report to spring training
in the morning.

241
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:59,887
We'll do our best to get you there
by tomorrow, but it might be the day after.

242
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:02,287
- Jack.
- Right this way.

243
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:07,766
You gave away our seats?

244
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,887
You get us back on that plane.

245
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,201
You get us back on that plane right now.

246
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:19,923
Do you wanna call the sheriff...

247
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:21,964
...or should I?

248
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,771
Watch your step.

249
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:44,287
Oop, there he is. There's my boy.

250
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:53,125
Folks, stand back,
we'll get the bags out.

251
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:56,647
Jackie Robinson.

252
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,845
Wendell Smith.

253
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,046
<i>Pittsburgh Courier.</i>

254
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:05,926
A reporter?

255
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:12,846
Mr. Rickey sent me to meet you.
I'm gonna be your Boswell.

256
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,041
My who?

257
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,486
Your chronicler.

258
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,848
Your advance man.

259
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,487
Hell, even your chauffeur.

260
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:22,971
Mrs. Robinson.

261
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,525
It's Rachel.

262
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:27,327
Man, you two looked wiped out.

263
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,521
You got a car?

264
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:32,444
Uh-huh.

265
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:39,367
Brooklyn plays downtown.
Montreal just a few blocks from here.

266
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:56,888
Joe and Duff Harris live here.

267
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:01,406
He gets out the Negro vote.
He does a lot of good for colored people.

268
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:04,161
Now, Mr. Rickey set it up himself.

269
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:07,720
"If the Robinsons can't stay
at the hotels...

270
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:10,963
...they should stay someplace
that represents something."

271
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:14,010
You'll stay here all but a few days
at the end of the week...

272
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:18,927
...when the Dodger organization goes
to Sanford. It's about 45 minutes away.

273
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:20,646
You'll stay here, Rachel.

274
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:23,844
This'll be your home
when Jackie has to travel.

275
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,609
Uh, where are the other wives staying?

276
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:30,001
Welcome to Daytona Beach.

277
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:33,041
- There are no other wives.
- You must be Jackie.

278
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:36,329
You're the only one that Mr. Rickey
allowed to spring training.

279
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:41,446
- Thank you.
- Mm-hm. After you.

280
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:44,601
Come on, now, skip.

281
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,768
All right, here we go, boys!

282
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,840
- I got it! I got it!
- I got it!

283
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:52,971
That was a pretty big hop, there.

284
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:54,360
- You got the hop!
- Ha, ha.

285
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:58,286
Spring training.
It's where we work out our differences.

286
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,645
All right!

287
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:13,963
You boys continue
to pretend you're ballplayers.

288
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,648
- Morning, Leo.
- Good morning, Mr. Rickey.

289
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:18,766
How are they doing?

290
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:22,641
They're rusty, but we'll have them
oiled up in no time, ready to go.

291
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,290
Oop.

292
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:31,049
First day of spring training.

293
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,851
Pittsburgh Courier readers need to know
how it feels.

294
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,011
It's okay.

295
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,082
That's not exactly a headline.

296
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,370
It's all I got.

297
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:49,488
Look, Jack, right now,
it's just me asking you.

298
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:52,843
<i>But there's gonna be The New York Times
and the Sporting News.</i>

299
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:56,322
- You should think about it.
- If they ask something, I'll answer it.

300
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:58,124
Okay, well here's one for you

301
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,886
What if one of these white pitchers
throws at you?

302
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:08,367
Look, they're gonna try to get under
your skin. You need to be ready.

303
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:10,329
Listen, listen.

304
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:13,091
You know...

305
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,083
You know how when you're
at the plate...

306
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:17,686
...you want to see the ball
come in slow?

307
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:21,004
You want to see these questions
come in slow too.

308
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:28,726
Hey, Jackie. Jackie, you think you can
make it with these white boys?

309
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:33,966
Uh, I had no problems with white men
in the service or at UCLA.

310
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:37,044
What you gonna do if one of these
pitchers throws at your head?

311
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,725
Yeah, Jack.

312
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,884
- I'll duck.
- Heh, that's a good one.

313
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:46,042
Hey, Jack, what's your natural position?

314
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:49,203
I've been playing shortstop.

315
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:51,931
Are you after Pee Wee Reese's job?

316
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:53,724
Uh...

317
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:55,723
Reese plays for Brooklyn.

318
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,969
I'm still trying to make Montreal.

319
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:01,647
Hey, Jack.
Hey, Jack, is this about politics?

320
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:03,046
It's about getting paid.

321
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:06,249
"About getting paid." Hear what he
said? "it's about getting paid."

322
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,526
He's gotta be kidding.

323
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,808
Yeah. Good luck, Hop.

324
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:15,130
Clay, Jackie Robinson.

325
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:19,922
Jackie, I'd like you to meet Clay Hopper.
Manager of the Montreal Royals.

326
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,481
Jack. They call me Hop.

327
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:26,446
Now, we ain't doing much today.
Just tossing the ball around, hitting a few.

328
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:30,002
You can probably toss with those fellows
over there.

329
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,123
Jorgensen, come here!

330
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:43,764
You're not playing him at shortstop,
huh, Clay?

331
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:47,521
Oh, he's getting by on a quick release.
His arm's too weak for short.

332
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:50,081
I think second base is his spot.

333
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,411
I agree.

334
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:55,725
Clay...

335
00:22:56,360 --> 00:23:01,002
...I need you to get the other players
to act like gentlemen around him.

336
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:03,049
Treat him like they would
any other teammate.

337
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,281
Hmm, mm-hm.

338
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:08,087
- Be natural, work together in harmony.
- Mm-hm.

339
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,246
Got the double up!

340
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:21,131
That was practically superhuman.

341
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,169
Heh, "superhuman"?

342
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:25,402
I mean, don't get carried away,
Mr. Rickey.

343
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:27,562
That's still a nigger out there.

344
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:35,167
Come on in now. Grab a bat. Who's up?

345
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,608
Nice job, boys!

346
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:44,922
Clay, I realize that attitude
is part of your cultural heritage.

347
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:49,688
That you practically nursed race prejudice
at your mother's breast...

348
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:51,888
...so I'll let that go.

349
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:56,330
But I will tell you this

350
00:23:56,480 --> 00:24:01,168
You will either manage Robinson fairly
and correctly...

351
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:04,649
...or you, sir, can be unemployed.

352
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,170
Yes, sir.

353
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:13,366
Let's go! Come on, guys, let's go!

354
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,921
Way to turn two, Jackie.

355
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,208
Well, well, lookie here.

356
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:31,409
Jackie, I'm Mr. Brock.

357
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,648
Welcome to Sanford, Florida.

358
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,643
Thank you for having us.

359
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:40,202
The day belongs
to decent-minded people.

360
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:44,400
- Wendell, always good to see you.
- You as well.

361
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:47,086
Yeah, well, the wife's inside cooking.

362
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:50,210
You know what she asked me?
She asked me this morning:

363
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:53,041
What do you serve when a hero's coming
to dinner?

364
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:56,409
Heh, um, Mr. Brock, I'm just a ballplayer.

365
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:57,721
Oh, no, no.

366
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:01,851
You tell that to all the little colored boys
playing baseball in Florida today.

367
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,288
To them, you a hero.

368
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:20,288
Here you go, ma'am.
Thank you, sir.

369
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,086
Here you go.

370
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:24,720
Scorecards, get your scorecards here!

371
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,765
Scorecards here!
Get your scorecards here!

372
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:33,804
Ed! You stay where I can see you.

373
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:36,611
Mom, I'm 10 years old!

374
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:38,450
Come on.

375
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:44,449
<i>Welcome to the inner-league
game between the Brooklyn Dodgers...</i>

376
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:47,211
<i>...and their Minor League affiliate,
the Montreal Royals.</i>

377
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:51,683
There you go, Pee Wee!

378
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:53,808
<i>Now coming to bat for the Royals...</i>

379
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:56,122
<i>...number nine, Jackie Robinson.</i>

380
00:25:58,040 --> 00:25:59,485
Get out of here!

381
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,961
Stand up tall, Jackie!

382
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,561
Get out, nigger!

383
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:07,326
Jack's got a thick skin. He'll be okay.

384
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:10,610
Well, how about you?

385
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:13,005
I better get one in a hurry, heh.

386
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,605
Have pride, Jackie!

387
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:23,084
Look. Look, there he is,
black as the ace of spades!

388
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:26,642
Hey, nigger boy!
What are you doing playing baseball?

389
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:28,040
Hit a home run, Jackie!

390
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:32,000
Please, God, let Jackie show them
what we can do.

391
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:35,488
- Please.
- All right, now, Jackie Robinson!

392
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:36,766
Let's go, Jackie!

393
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:56,090
Come on, Jackie!

394
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,367
Ball!

395
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:11,203
They're giving you a chance!
Do something about it!

396
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:16,880
Let's go, Higbe!
Shut him down right here!

397
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,290
Ball!

398
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:25,962
Durocher,
tell him to throw some strikes!

399
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,241
Let him hit!

400
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:28,890
Come on now, come on now!

401
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:31,367
He ain't scared of you, Higbe!

402
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,890
You show him, Jackie!

403
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,161
Ball!

404
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:41,969
Come on, rook.
Ain't you gonna swing at something?

405
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:46,250
Higbe, just settle down. Let's get
the ball over the plate now, all right?

406
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,404
Ball four!

407
00:27:57,600 --> 00:28:00,126
You stink, Higbe!

408
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:04,251
It's just a walk.

409
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,688
Ha, ha, who can blame them?

410
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,487
Good job, Jackie.

411
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:11,610
<i>Now coming to bat for the Royals...</i>

412
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:13,603
<i>...number 3, Spider Jorgensen.</i>

413
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,321
Let's go, Hig!

414
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:21,289
All right, Higbe, shake it off, there.

415
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,807
We got this, boy. We got this, boy.
Let's do it.

416
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:30,284
Well, throw it over there!
What are you waiting for?

417
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:33,724
Safe!

418
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,970
Come on, pop up, Jack.

419
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:01,810
Ball one!

420
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,844
Yeah, Jackie!

421
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,809
Heads up, Jack. Get the sign.

422
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:33,960
He's going!
Runner! Runner!

423
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:35,721
Come on, move!
Get back!

424
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:37,604
Get him, Schultzy!
Get him, Schultzy!

425
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:41,045
Here we go!

426
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,009
What are you gonna do now?
Come on!

427
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:44,321
Outside! Outside!

428
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:47,211
On your horse, Bragan!
On your horse! Outside!

429
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:50,045
- Now!
- Go, Stanky! Go, Stank!

430
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:53,727
Ooh.

431
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,561
Hey, all right!

432
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:36,248
Hey! Don't you know nothing?

433
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:38,882
You're supposed to get back
when I step off.

434
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:47,529
What are you doing? You can dance
with him later! Focus on the plate!

435
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:52,004
Come on, now! Work the plate!
Work the plate!

436
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:04,127
Come on, Higbe, don't worry about
the runner. Get this guy at the plate.

437
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,206
Timeout!

438
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:10,486
That's a balk.

439
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,808
Runner, take home.

440
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:18,245
Son of a bitch.

441
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:24,288
He didn't come to play, he came to kill.

442
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:29,442
What happened? I don't understand.

443
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:33,730
The pitcher dropped the ball. It's a balk.
Therefore, Jackie scores.

444
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:35,484
But he didn't do anything.

445
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:39,850
Oh, Mama, yes, he did.
He discombobulated the man.

446
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:42,361
He... What?

447
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,809
Phew.

448
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:48,401
I hope Jackie's sleeping all right.

449
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:52,690
Chasing baseballs in the sun all day?
Put me in my grave.

450
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:01,931
- How they treating him out there?
- Well, they treat him okay.

451
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,248
As far as I can see.

452
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:13,408
Well, you can find good people
every place.

453
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:17,127
Even here in Sanford.

454
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:21,685
Is he in there?

455
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:26,647
Who is it that you're looking for?

456
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:28,450
The Nigra ballplayer.

457
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,329
Is he in there?

458
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:37,648
He's asleep right now.

459
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,170
Maybe you wanna come back
in the morning.

460
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,767
No, I ain't coming back.

461
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:46,401
Other fellas is coming.

462
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:50,807
And they ain't happy
that he's staying here in Sanford...

463
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:53,930
...playing ball with white boys.

464
00:32:56,160 --> 00:33:00,290
- Now, let me tell you something, sir.
- No, you listen to me, young man.

465
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:03,802
You best just skedaddle on out of here.

466
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:07,602
Because if they get here
and he's still here...

467
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:09,644
...there's gonna be trouble.

468
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:11,930
You understand?

469
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:13,805
Trouble.

470
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:16,926
Trouble, trouble, trouble.

471
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,291
Mr. Brock.

472
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:26,648
May I please use your telephone?

473
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:29,287
Wake him up and get him out of there.

474
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:34,168
Put him in the car and, uh, start driving
to Daytona Beach. Now.

475
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,846
Uh, oh, and, uh, Wendell...

476
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:43,406
...under no circumstances are you
to tell him what this is about, uh...

477
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:47,766
I don't want him getting it in his head...

478
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:49,962
...to stay there and fight.

479
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:24,171
Where's he at?

480
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:27,085
I don't know.
Think he's getting another one.

481
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:29,721
Hey, Jim. You escorting
that boy out of town?

482
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,001
Hey, look at this.

483
00:34:31,160 --> 00:34:32,764
What's that?

484
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,731
What's he want?

485
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,684
Hey, hey, hey!

486
00:34:49,680 --> 00:34:51,170
What the hell, Wendell?

487
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:53,766
A man came by while you was asleep.

488
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:55,490
He said more men were coming.

489
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:57,165
It might have been those fellas.

490
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:00,011
Mr. Rickey said to get you to Daytona
Beach ASAP.

491
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:02,530
Why didn't you say so?

492
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:06,526
Mr. Rickey was afraid you wouldn't leave.
You'd want to stay there and fight.

493
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:11,766
Man, what in the hell
are you laughing at?

494
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:15,123
I thought you woke me
because I was cut from the team.

495
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:23,401
You got a strange sense of humor, man.

496
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:33,407
Two, two, two! Take him back.
Throw him out now!

497
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:36,847
Safe!

498
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,363
You're too fast for them, Jackie!

499
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:46,602
All right, way to go. Way to go, boy!

500
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:48,444
Get that nigger off the field!

501
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:51,331
Come on, Spider, bring him in. Let's go.

502
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,486
We got him.

503
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,209
Four! Four! Four!

504
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:15,249
No cut!
He's running through!

505
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,325
Safe!

506
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:24,006
Get off the field.

