535
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:48,007
A lot of folks around here
feel the same way.

536
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:52,483
If a man's got the goods,
he deserves a fair chance, that's all.

537
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:56,205
Ma'am.

538
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:11,400
You wanted to see me, Mr. Rickey?

539
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:15,084
Bermuda grass grows so well here.

540
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:18,562
I wish we could get it to grow like this up
in Brooklyn.

541
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,725
Yeah.

542
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,363
I like the way it smells
when they mow it.

543
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:28,205
Heh, me too.

544
00:38:29,560 --> 00:38:31,050
Jackie...

545
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:35,041
...it is my pleasure...

546
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:39,410
...to tell you that you have earned a place
with the Montreal Royals.

547
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:45,568
When they head north on Tuesday
for opening day with Jersey City...

548
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:47,922
...you'll be on the train.

549
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:52,851
I won't let you down.

550
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,411
Yeah, I know you won't.

551
00:38:56,920 --> 00:39:00,606
If you don't mind,
I'd like to go tell my wife.

552
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:03,366
Ah, you give her my regards.

553
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:11,607
Mr. Rickey?

554
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:16,289
Why are you doing this?

555
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:24,127
I'm in the baseball business.

556
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:28,289
With you and the other Negro players
I hope to bring up next year...

557
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:31,967
...I can put together a team
that can win the World Series.

558
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:35,124
And the World Series means money.

559
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,007
You believe that, don't you?

560
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:42,081
I don't think it matters what I believe.

561
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,930
Only what I do.

562
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:46,651
Agreed.

563
00:39:47,480 --> 00:39:49,084
Therefore...

564
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:52,483
...I want you to worry those pitchers
till they come apart.

565
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,642
Run as you see fit.

566
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:57,371
Sometimes you'll get caught,
but that doesn't matter.

567
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:59,648
Ty Cobb got caught plenty.

568
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:02,485
You just run those bases
like the devil himself.

569
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:05,849
Put the natural fear of God in them.

570
00:40:08,160 --> 00:40:09,525
Yes, sir.

